00:28:01.950 --> 00:28:02.940
SHANNON HARVEY: OK.

00:28:02.940 --> 00:28:05.620
So the first thing is that this
is an independent film, which

00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:10.080
means that my husband and
I financed it ourselves.

00:28:10.080 --> 00:28:12.260
So we don't have a
big studio behind us,

00:28:12.260 --> 00:28:15.230
and we don't have a lot of
money that's driving it.

00:28:15.230 --> 00:28:17.010
But we released the
film independently,

00:28:17.010 --> 00:28:19.930
which meant that we did
a tour around Australia,

00:28:19.930 --> 00:28:22.320
and around the
US, and in the UK,

00:28:22.320 --> 00:28:29.452
where we showed it to a lot of
people through wellness groups

00:28:29.452 --> 00:28:30.910
and through chronic
illness groups.

00:28:33.970 --> 00:28:35.600
It was just so well-received.

00:28:35.600 --> 00:28:37.360
It was so humbling.

00:28:37.360 --> 00:28:42.370
In fact, at our US premiere,
which was in Massachusetts,

00:28:42.370 --> 00:28:46.760
just outside of Boston, we
had a panel discussion where--

00:28:46.760 --> 00:28:49.890
on the panel was, obviously,
myself, Jon Kabat-Zinn

00:28:49.890 --> 00:28:53.460
from the film, a
neuroscientist, a pediatrician.

00:28:53.460 --> 00:28:58.530
And also, we had the CEO of
Massachusetts General Hospital

00:28:58.530 --> 00:29:02.280
and a health care group
that's responsible for 60%

00:29:02.280 --> 00:29:04.700
of the health care in the
state of Massachusetts.

00:29:04.700 --> 00:29:06.920
And his name's Dr. Eric Dickson.

00:29:06.920 --> 00:29:09.560
And his response was incredible.

00:29:09.560 --> 00:29:12.760
He stated that he wanted
to make it compulsory

00:29:12.760 --> 00:29:15.810
viewing for first-year
medical students.

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:18.110
Then he decided he'd add
fourth-year medical students

00:29:18.110 --> 00:29:18.830
as well.

00:29:18.830 --> 00:29:20.895
So they go to it at the
beginning and at the end.

00:29:20.895 --> 00:29:23.270
And then he added that he was
going to make his residents

00:29:23.270 --> 00:29:25.110
and his doctors
and all the people

00:29:25.110 --> 00:29:26.910
involved in his
health care see it.

00:29:26.910 --> 00:29:29.970
So that was such an
amazing response.

00:29:29.970 --> 00:29:33.150
And I know, particularly
for the people who

00:29:33.150 --> 00:29:36.180
are from the mindfulness-based
stress reduction clinic

00:29:36.180 --> 00:29:39.460
there in Massachusetts, it
was a big moment for them,

00:29:39.460 --> 00:29:44.760
because they felt like
finally, the medical world

00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:47.660
and their world was
coming together.

00:29:47.660 --> 00:29:48.800
So that's been really good.

00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:50.820
And we've got a
program, which we

00:29:50.820 --> 00:29:53.450
call Host Your Own
Screening of the Film,

00:29:53.450 --> 00:29:55.050
